8232, "(fr)Take a deep breath, everyone. This was a challenging operation, and that you came back at all is testament to your skills. Station raids are never easy, so I won't keep you here longer than needed. Let's get started."
8233, "(fr)The STX refinery itself was a total loss, but under the circumstances, this is to be expected. Thanks to your skill, the station was fully evacuated, and the Ifrit and both transport wings made the jump to Amanu without issue. Captain Courtemanche and the transport crews send their thanks. You far exceeded expectations today. The wounded are being transferred to the Gregor as we speak, and many of the refinery crew have expressed a desire to lend their technical skills to the defense effort. Well done.

Not only is this a victory from a humanitarian perspective, but it further solidifies our working relationship with the LNA navy. The LNA's Security Director Abe has asked me to send you their way to receive the New Alliance Star in recognition of your efforts today. The ceremony is at 1800 this Thursday, so put up as good a showing there as you did here."
8234, "(fr)The STX refinery itself was a total loss, but under the circumstances, this is to be expected. In spite of fierce enemy resistance, you held off ADEIS's attack long enough for most of the crew to evacuate to the Ifrit. They're being transferred to the Gregor and Amanu Station as we speak, and I've heard that some of the survivors intend to lend their technical skills to the defense effort."
8235, "(fr)The STX refinery itself was a total loss. Under the circumstances, it's fortunate that as many of the crew made it off the station as did. The survivors are being transferred to Amanu Station, and the Gregor is taking on the wounded as capacity frees up. The LNA's response so far has been muted. No one feels good about this outcome, but at least our allies understood we did the best we could."
8236, "(fr)The STX refinery itself was a total loss. Under the circumstances, it's fortunate that as many of the crew made it off the station as did. The survivors are being transferred to Amanu Station, and the Gregor is taking on the wounded as capacity frees up. The LNA has expressed their disappointment in our response, and Captain Jers has her hands full playing diplomat. She's asked that we stay away from the memorial services to avoid an incident."
8237, "(fr)Tactical analysis of the battle indicates that the Lambda and Tau transports were a weak point in our plan. Unfortunately, this has become something of a problem. Our Elysium wings have been stretched thin ferrying civilians between safe zones, and the losses we sustained here will only exacerbate the situation. These past few weeks have highlighted in sharp relief just how fragile the design is, but we have to make do with what's available to us. We simply don't have the Isis tonnage to replace them. This was a complicated engagement with many moving parts, and I don't have any great tactical insights. We simply have to prioritize transport escort more heavily."
8238, "(fr)Tactical analysis of the battle indicates that the Lambda and Tau transports were a weak point in our plan. Unfortunately, this has become something of a problem. Our Elysium wings have been stretched thin ferrying civilians between safe zones, and the losses we sustained here will only exacerbate the situation. These past few weeks have highlighted in sharp relief just how fragile the design is, but we have to make do with what's available to us. We simply don't have the Isis tonnage to replace them. Our losses sting particularly hard since we had to abort the evacuation with the loss of all four transports."
8239, "(fr)Tactical analysis of the battle indicates the Ifrit's missile defenses were overwhelmed by enemy fire. While she and the Izanami have performed far above expectations so far, they are not armored to the same level as a modern warship, and must be protected appropriately. Had she remained in the CZ longer, she would have been able to onboard more civilians. Additionally, the strain forced Captain Courtemanche to expend a significant portion of his onboard missile supply in this battle, and replacements are becoming scarce. We'll need to be careful about how we deploy this ship going forward."
8240, "(fr)Additionally, during the battle, we deployed a freighter wing to recover some of the refinery's outlying materiel and deny it to the enemy. These ships made it back to Amanu with their cargo successfully. All supplies are valuable right now, and you did well in supporting their mission along with everything else going on."
8241, "(fr)If there's a silver lining to be had here, it's that we were able to recover some of the refinery's outlying materiel and deny it to the enemy. The Thêta wing freighters made it back to Amanu with their cargo successfully. All supplies are valuable right now, and this op will certainly help mitigate the loss of the refinery."
8242, "(fr)The Ifrit and Lavoisier have returned to their posts in Amanu's defense screen. Security Director Abe asked me to convey their thanks for bringing those ships home intact. The Lavoisier's holograms continue to be an effective force multiplier, and on a diplomatic level, Dr. Sarno has been invaluable in coordinating operations with the LNA and SDA. While the Ifrit and Izanami have performed far above expectations so far, the Ifrit expended a significant portion of its onboard missile supply in this battle, and replacements are becoming scarce. We'll need to be careful about how we deploy this ship going forward."
8243, "(fr)In the aftermath of the battle, LNA observer units deployed to get long-range sensors on the op site. The force with which the refinery blew seems to have taken IN.E.D.A.M.01 by surprise. While the ship was able to initiate subspace, the explosion left it with no salvage worth recovering. Analysis of existing telemetry suggests it may have sustained internal damage to its launch bays, which were exposed to the explosion and therefore vulnerable. The possibility of baiting IN.E.D.A.M.01 with a “poison pill” is being discussed, if we can come up with an explosive of appropriate magnitude and a means of disguising it."
8244, "(fr)Given the total destruction of the refinery, it likely goes without saying that we will not attempt SAR."
