8927, "(fr)ADEIS besieges the distant Adhara system. GTA forces aboard the captured Taouret are in hot pursuit."
8928, "(fr)!html Okay, cramming two wings, my Centaur, and an Isis into this hangar is giving me academy dorm flashbacks. Holly says we've got 75 minutes, so we're swapping in Locuste racks and patching up what we can. Stay in your cockpits and out of my way. It smells better, anyway, trust me. One, a couple HoL fighters survived the capture op. I pulled the interlingual firmware before we left, so let me know if you want them. The captain sent a message with it. Uploading it to your fighters now.

Pilots, I have no idea what you're flying into, but you've proven yourselves to be some of the finest I've ever served with. I know you'll make the right choices. We'll hold out here in Luyten. The drones seem intent on taking down Amanu, but we beat them once, and we can do it again. Contact GTA Command and advise them of our situation, then intercept IN.E.D.A.M.01 and put a stop to whatever it's keen on doing. Good luck."
8929, "(fr)Stop IN.E.D.A.M.01"
8930, "(fr)Follow IN.E.D.A.M.01"
8932, "(fr)Destroy Jamming Antenna"
8933, "(fr)Destroy IN.E.D.A.M.01."
8934, "(fr)Wait for GTA response force."
8935, "(fr)Where the hell are we?"
8936, "(fr)My navcomputer is collecting astrographics now. Standby."
8937, "(fr)Belay that, Opportunité. We're in Adhara. The Krios did a stint here."
8938, "(fr)Adhara? ...Oh, hell."
8939, "(fr)Eh? What's the problem?"
8940, "(fr)Aside from the rogue command carrier? ADEIS didn't just scrap the Taouret. It copied it. It's going to hop around the HoL network and come back to Luyten stronger than ever."
8941, "(fr)Er, what's that gotta do with Adhara?"
8942, "(fr)Ever vacationed here? Adhara isn't exactly a backwater system. There're billions of kilos of luxury orbital for ADEIS to repurpose."
8943, "(fr)We need to get a message to GTA Command. Now."
8944, "(fr)Already tried. Non-local comms are red, and I've got one guess as to why."
8945, "(fr)Well, we can't kill that without backup. Anyone got a bright idea?"
8946, "(fr)I do. I'm setting course for the Epsilon Pegasi node. Once we're clear of the jamming, we'll explain the situation, then switch to sprint drives and get help for Luyten."
8947, "(fr)Can you make it in time?"
8948, "(fr)I'm very good at my job, Alpha 3."
8949, "(fr)Elias, tell them... Tell any GTA forces you meet that Case Apollyon has been declared."
8950, "(fr)Copy that. Helm, engage subspace drives."
8951, "(fr)Heads up, I see Ankous and Iseuts heading our way!"
8952, "(fr)Taouret, you need to move away from the jump device. We've no idea how much longer it will last."
8953, "(fr)We cannot. The field engine repair did not hold. All of our crew is boarding the Qetesh. Stand by."
8954, "(fr)Pilots, we have cleared Taouret's fighterbay. It is unfortunate to abandon such a unique ship, but we had no choice."
8955, "(fr)Er, what's the plan here? I don't think we can hold until reinforcements arrive."
8956, "(fr)We just-- Hang on."
8957, "(fr)Energy spikes from the Lascaux, get clear!"
8958, "(fr)IN.E.D.A.M.01 is jumping out! Has anyone got a SUTRAC fix on that thing?"
8959, "(fr)Negative SUTRAC, but Rosemary's right. It's going to Annwn. The capital planet. Dozens of orbitals, enough material for thousands of drones, and tens of thousands of lives aboard."
8960, "(fr)Then what the hell are we waiting for?! One, we need to get to the nearest orbital, now!"
8961, "(fr)I'm right behind you guys."
8962, "(fr)As are we. We will set our guns for torpedo intercept."
8963, "(fr)GTA Command, this is Ensign Kumagi, 508th Loaded Dice. Come in."
8964, "(fr)Loaded Dice, this is Malendroke Flight. Warbook puts your squad in Luyten. What are you doing here?"
8965, "(fr)No time to explain. Tell your admiral that a major attack is about to light up over Annwn. We're heading there now. We'll contact you again once we've cleared local jamming."
8966, "(fr)Local jamming? Explain yourself, pilot! We need more information."
8967, "(fr)We're about to lose contact. Scramble your fighters to the Annwn orbitals. Contact all local transports capable of evac. We'll need all the help we can get. 508th clear."
8968, "(fr)Jump coordinates set. There's only one orbital that's showing zero comm traffic. Exarch-class habitat."
8969, "(fr)Shit. What do we do?"
8970, "(fr)We have to clear the jamming. We can't evac these people if we can't call for more ships."
8971, "(fr)How do we do that?"
8972, "(fr)It's gotta be those four antennae starboard side. I betcha wrecking those'll clear the comms."
8973, "(fr)What about those transports? We can't leave them alone."
