4496, "(fr)Welcome to Between the Ashes: Slaves of Chaos. This is the first of our main campaign releases; there's also a two-mission prologue, Mefistofele, which takes place around the start of this campaign. If you'd like to know more about the world, feel free to check out the reference material in the tech room, or follow along with the broader story in the news room. Whether you engage with all the supplemental material or play through the missions on their own, we hope you enjoy your time in our world.<br/><br/>'Slaves of Chaos originally released back in 2016, and began as a way for me to learn Freespace mission design. In fact, the project served as a starting point for most members of the team as we learned the basics of game design. Most of the original team has long since moved on to other things, but I am still proud of this game and what we were able to create together.' ~ Mike Nelson, Project Lead"
4497, "(fr)Every mission in the main campaign of Between the Ashes has a secret object hidden somewhere. Scan them all to unlock a special playable ship! If you need a hint, you can press Alt-3. There are also several hidden arcade missions. The unlock conditions are different for each of them, but usually involve discovering some secret during campaign missions. Once unlocked, you can play them through the simulator in the barracks."
4498, "(fr)Welcome to Between the Ashes: The Growing Silence. This is the second of our main campaign releases, and it follows a few years after the events of the 2-mission prologue campaign, Antwerp. If you'd like to know more about the world, feel free to check out the reference material in the tech room, or follow along with the broader story in the news room. Whether you engage with all the supplemental material or play through the missions on their own, we hope you enjoy your time in our world.<br/><br/>'This release marks a sort of reboot for Between the Ashes; it has an entirely new development team and a renewed vision on game design. TGS has been in my brain for nearly a decade and the development team has been bringing it to life for the better part of five years. We're so happy with how it's turned out. With Naomi's incredible talent with words and Kyle's skill with mission design, I feel this game is better than anything I imagined so many years ago. So with that out of the way, please enjoy The Growing Silence.' ~ Mike Nelson, Project Lead"
