1022, "(fr)The Fourteen Years War and the Great War made abundantly clear the importance of controlling jump nodes, and mine and minesweeping technology developed in parallel. Even today, the Antarès Federation and the Hammer of Light use mines to secure the nodes leading into their systems. The Carillon is the raiders' entry, typically seeded in expectation of a jump node shift. This nuisance behavior was at odds with typical raider tactics, which otherwise emphasized high mobility and overwhelming numbers. During the Lavoisier's ill-fated expedition to Laramis, however, an alternate configuration of the Carillon was encountered, which sacrificed explosive yield for a high-precision jump drive, allowing it to strike like a torpedo from subspace. Fortunately, this weapon seems to require a raider vessel on station to provide coordinates, which can be jammed by readily available electronics warfare options. Until the raider command staff are safely in custody, standing orders are for all Allied convoys throughout Luyten to include at least one ship carrying such a jammer."
731, "(fr)The Hippocrates is a hospital ship currently entering service with the GTA. Its on-board facilities can provide top-of-the-line medical care to thousands of patients at once, and can easily reconfigure to a refugee transport if needed. The unusual design of the vessel, atypical of any spaceframe seen before it, is a deliberate design choice - any of the Hippocrates' main sections can be isolated from the rest of the ship in the event of a breached hull or quarantine. Currently, the GTA operates a small number of Hippocrates units in struggling war-torn systems, and is actively trying to push the design into civilian service as well."
