1483, "(fr)The EM Pulse missile is conceptually similar to the Stiletto, featuring a warhead tuned for electronics warfare rather than simple hull damage. Unlike the Stiletto, the EMP produced by the weapon is in no way focused, thus creating a shockwave that disrupts the electronic systems of any enemy ships caught within it. EM Pulse missiles are most effective against bombers, as they disrupt the targeting computers for bombs and prevent them from acquiring lock on enemy ships."
