1248, "(fr)The prosaically-named Cluster Bomb is a GTI-designed successor to the Synaptic. Like the Synaptic, the Cluster Bomb splits apart to produce a flurry of explosive $quotebomblets$quote which automatically target nearby fighters and bombers. Unlike the Synaptic, the Cluster Bomb has been well-received by bomber squadrons: it is considerably more effective at destroying fighters outright, and can even inflict meaningful damage to soft targets like transports should the tactical situation require it. However, the Cluster Bomb lacks the Synaptic's ability to disrupt entire fighter wings, and some pilots continue to carry the older weapon as a suppression tool."
1129, "(fr)Synaptic Variant, Wing Attack, Area Effect"
1127, "(fr)GTM-86 Cluster Bomb"
1126, "(fr)Cluster Bomb"
1125, "(fr)The Synaptic suppression bomb, nicknamed the Earthshaker, is an anti-fighter weapon intended for use by bombers. The Synaptic travels a good distance away from the bomber launching it before detonating, creating a disruptive shockwave that rattles any enemy pilots caught in it. This explosion also helps propel multiple independent $quotebomblets$quote, which automatically target nearby enemy fighters. While classified as a bomb, the Synaptic is only effective in a fighter suppression role, and has very little killing power on its own. Limited numbers of Synaptics remain in production, but it is expected that a next-generation system will replace it."
1124, "(fr)Anti-Fighter Bomb, Wing Attack, Area Effect"
