10631, "(fr)The Shield Pack was developed by the Luyten New Alliance to facilitate operations within the highly energetic Doceitov anomaly. Adapted from the miniature shield projector carried by Stiletto missiles, the Shield Pack is capable of emitting a short-lived, high-intensity pulse which rapidly re-energizes the shields of the firing ship. The LNA designed the Shield Pack both for their own use and for sale to the GTA, and is designed to be compatible with capacitors taking from the defunct ML-16 weapon. The Shield Pack's prototypical status carries some technical limitations, such as the inability to recharge the system without the aid of a support ship."
10630, "(fr)2-Second Shield Overcharge,
Call Support To Reload"
10714, "(fr)Shield Pack"
10629, "(fr)The Magnetic Grapple is a common civilian tool typically mounted on shuttles and transports at spaceborne dockyards. The grapple utilizes a resonant magnetic field to effectively latch onto an object at distance, allowing it to be slowly and carefully manipulated by the ship or drone equipped with it. These devices are most commonly used by utility ships in large cargo depots, where they allow for the repositioning of cargo containers without the logistical expenses of spinning up a freighter."
10628, "(fr)50hw Magnetic Grapple"
10627, "(fr)Mag Grapple"
1079, "(fr)The Force-CXI is a launcher system for the CXI series of tracking devices. The CXI bug has the ability to record information from enemy communication systems, and automatically links with GTA communication platforms to allow for remote tracking of a tagged ship through multiple systems. The Force-CXI was originally designed by GTI for special operations use, but has become a common sight among customs enforcement units, who use it to ensure suspect ships cannot easily escape into subspace."
1487, "(fr)The Barracuda torpedo is the oldest weapon still in mainline use with the Parliamentary Vasudan Navy, having been in their inventories since the start of the Terran-Vasudan War over fifteen years ago. The Barracuda is a small-scale nuclear weapon, capable of causing significant harm to cruisers and stationary objects. Vasudan engineers have modified most Barracudas to be capable of firing both in an aspect-seeking and in a dumbfire role, allowing for flexibility heavier ordnance does not have. The Barracuda is the lightest anti-warship weapon in service, and even mainline PVN squadrons often carry the jointly designed Tsunami instead."
1078, "(fr)Tracking Beacon, Extremely Low Damage"
1077, "(fr)Force-CXI Target Acquisition"
1075, "(fr)With stocks of argon depleting for use in the various Prometheus variants in service, GTA engineers have been forced to improvise new means to maintain the otherwise useless weapons. By replacing the argon injector of the Prometheus with an EM modulator derived from the Banshee, the Prometheus R was created, allowing for older weapons to be retrofitted to working order. Due to its experimental design, the Prometheus R is somewhat temperamental. While it boasts slightly higher hull damage than the HL-7, some pilots prefer to use the HL-7 even in assault roles for its flexibility."
10626, "(fr)Anti-Hull Weapon, EMP Effect Disorients Targets"
1074, "(fr)GTW-5R Prometheus Retrofit"
1073, "(fr)Prometheus R"
1072, "(fr)The Akheton Corporation's entry into the SDG market is a Vasudan upgrade of the GTW-41a. Intended to be even more effective than its predecessor, the Akheton SDG is compatible with both Terran and Vasudan fighters, and is significantly cheaper to produce than the Disruptor. It is expected that the Akheton SDG will become the standard subsystem destroyer for the foreseeable future."
1069, "(fr)PVW Akheton SDG"
1068, "(fr)Akheton SDG"
1066, "(fr)The Mekhu HL-7 is a derivative of the Terran-created Subach HL-7. The Mekhu applies Vasudan combat philosophy to the original design, having less individual damage per bolt but a notably higher rate of fire when compared to the Subach. Like the Subach, the Mekhu has been well accepted by Vasudan pilots, particularly when utilized in the quad bank of Thot or Tauret fighters where its full rate of fire can be put to effective use against Hammer of Light renegades."
1065, "(fr)Vasudan HL-7,
High Fire Rate,
Slightly Less Damage"
