1063, "(fr)Mekhu HL-7"
10625, "(fr)Subach HL-7"
1062, "(fr)Subach-Innes' HL-7 is intended as a successor to the Avenger. The weapon uses the same fundamental paradigm of a physical core encased in excited plasma, and this hybrid approach has once again demonstrated exceptional energy efficiency. The Subach HL-7 differs primarily in its excitement mechanism: a ring of highly focused xasers surrounding the primary emitter. The HL-7's per-unit cost has been criticized as excessive, and its internal heat sinks have shown themselves to be somewhat lacking, creating a maintenance hassle. Nevertheless, the HL-7's combination of a high rate of fire, good effect against both hulls and shields, and efficiency have made it an instant favorite with Fleet pilots. As the Avenger struggles to keep up with modern shields and Prometheus stocks decline, the HL-7 has been pushed into the role of a standard-issue primary weapon."
10624, "(fr)High Hull/Average Shield Damage, Low Power Draw"
1061, "(fr)GTW Subach HL-7"
1060, "(fr)Subach HL-7"
1059, "(fr)The Leech Cannon utilizes a self-destructive plasma burst to act as a miniature split-second capacitor, draining the energy of enemy afterburners, shields, and energy weapons. In practice, however, it has been disliked for its inability to cause any serious form of harm to enemy ships. Early stages of development are underway to replace the Leech with a more effective weapon capable of performing the same duties."
1058, "(fr)Tactical Weapon, Drains Energy, Low Damage"
1057, "(fr)GTW-43 Leech Cannon"
1056, "(fr)Leech Cannon"
1055, "(fr)Designed as a special-issue upgrade to the standard Prometheus, the Prometheus A was used extensively by both rebel and loyalist GTI forces during the Hades Rebellion. This variant offered even higher damage than the original at the expense of slightly increased power draw. Much like the original Prometheus, the Prometheus A has become vanishingly rare after the collapse of the Sol jump node."
1054, "(fr)GTW-5A Prometheus Advanced"
1053, "(fr)Prometheus A"
1052, "(fr)The Prometheus was based around advanced argon laser technology, utilizing a fully out-of-phase projectile system to engage enemy targets. While slightly less effective against shielding than the Avenger, it was much more capable against enemy ship hulls, and thus became the weapon of choice against the more durable but less thickly shielded ships of Terran criminals and Hammer of Light renegades. The Prometheus became a workhorse weapon during the Shivan Incursion. However, the loss of the Sol jump node cut off access to Earth's supply of argon, cutting Prometheus production virtually to nil."
1051, "(fr)Hull-Attack Weapon,
Average Shield Damage"
1050, "(fr)Prometheus"
1049, "(fr)The Shield Breaker, commonly referred to as the S-Breaker, is a prototype weapon developed by GTI. The S-Breaker is an electromagnetic weapon much like the Banshee, but it is highly modulated, linking with the sensors of the firing craft to calculate an optimal anti-frequency for disrupting the target’s shields. This has a downside, however, as the Shield Breaker is physically incapable of harming enemy subsystems or hulls. The S-Breaker has proven effective in concert with a hull-penetrating weapon such as the Prometheus R. It also boasts an unusually long range, making for an effective initiation weapon."
1048, "(fr)Long-Range Shield Breaker, No Hull Damage"
1047, "(fr)GTW-99 Shield Breaker"
1046, "(fr)S-Breaker"
10623, "(fr)The Railgun Evo is a development of the GTW Railgun prototype weapon that was developed by Galactic Terran Intelligence before and during the Hades Rebellion. Though the GTA abandoned the Railgun as too slow and unwieldy for conventional combat, the Second Dawn Society later revisited the concept. The Railgun Evo functions in a conceptually equivalent manner, but adds auxiliary gauss coils around the rails for better guidance, and a sabot made of newly-developed collapsed-core molybdenum. Though the sabot's increased density allows it to damage hulls notably better than the original Railgun, unstable molecular bonding make it even less effective against energy shielding than the original."
10621, "(fr)GTW-65d Railgun Evo"
10620, "(fr)Railgun Evo"
1045, "(fr)A GTI prototype cannon, the Railgun was originally developed as an attempt to penetrate the shields of the Lucifer superdestroyer. The weapon uses a series of electromagnets firing with millisecond precision to accelerate caseless uranium slugs at extreme velocity. While its range, accuracy, and impact force are the highest in the Terran arsenal, it has proven ineffective in its intended anti-shield role. The weapon also suffers from an extended recharge cycle. Although the Railgun is technically a ballistic weapon, the slugs are extremely small, and for tactical purposes the quantity of ammunition is unlimited."
1044, "(fr)Long-Range Anti-Hull Weapon, Long Recharge Cycle"
1043, "(fr)GTW-65 Railgun"
1042, "(fr)Railgun"
10619, "(fr)Banshee"
10618, "(fr)Banshee"
1041, "(fr)Developed by Galactic Terran Intelligence well before their betrayal of the GTA, the Banshee is a plasma-vectored electromagnetic pulse weapon. The Banshee’s rapid pulses of exceptionally strong electromagnetic energy were intended to quickly chew apart the shields of Shivan ships, which had limited hull strength and shielding far more capable than Terran or Vasudan fighters. The weapon's name comes from the sonic disturbance reported by pilots firing the weapon. While the Banshee is effective in its role, its high cost combined the disappearance of the Shivans from known space has resulted in it becoming limited issue, though the concepts it introduced will likely see use in future weapon designs.<br/><br/>Like the Avenger, the Banshee has a turret variant, typically mounted on Ursa and Amon strategic bombers."
1040, "(fr)EM Weapon, High Power Draw, Extreme Shield Damage"
1039, "(fr)GTW-7 Banshee"
1038, "(fr)Banshee"
1037, "(fr)The GTW-32 Flail is a rapid-fire, low-energy weapon originally developed from scientific equipment. The Flail was intended to disrupt Shivan shields and inflicts very little hull damage$semicolon however, it has shown itself to be unexpectedly effective as a kinetic weapon, knocking enemy strikecraft off their intended course and making them vulnerable to a follow-up attack. Sustained Flail fire can even $quotepin$quote less maneuverable fighters and bombers. Some pilots have also had experience using the Flail as a bomb intercept weapon, leveraging its high rate of fire to prematurely detonate enemy warheads."
1036, "(fr)Low Power Draw,
Kinetic Effect,
Moderate Shield Damage"
