11036, "(fr)Welcome to SCS-1-Bêta, Combat Training. In this simulation, you will learn weapon controls and dogfighting tactics."
11037, "(fr)An Elysium-class transport has been added to the simulation. Obtain aspect lock on it. Try using your Target Object Under Reticle control this time. [Press $Y$]"
11038, "(fr)Good. Fire a single Interceptor missile at the transport. [Press $Spacebar$] You may also want to match its speed [$M$]."
11039, "(fr)Your secondary banks can be set to fire one or two missiles at a time. Enable dual-fire mode now. [Press $Shift-/$]"
11040, "(fr)Good. Now fire two Interceptors. [Press $Spacebar$]"
11041, "(fr)Set your missiles back to single-fire mode. [Press $Shift-/$]"
11042, "(fr)Now we'll practice with the Disruptor cannon. The Disruptor is an anti-subsystem weapon, typically used to disable engine systems and disarm turrets. Arm your Disruptor, and only your Disruptor. [Press $.$]"
11043, "(fr)Good. Target the transport's engine subsystem. [Press $S$]"
11044, "(fr)Get within weapon range, then open fire on the transport's engine with your Disruptor. Stop when it shows as disabled in your target view."
11045, "(fr)Well done. Now destroy the transport's weapon subsystem. If the subsystem is marked with a diamond, this means the transport's hull is in the way$semicolon move in front of the transport until it becomes a square."
11046, "(fr)Transports and warships are armed with turrets. Destroying their weapon control centers will impair their accuracy, but not stop the turrets from firing."
11047, "(fr)Elysium transports have only a single turret. Target it now. [Press $K$]"
11048, "(fr)Good. Now disarm the transport with your Disruptor. As with normal subsystems, turrets are marked with a square if they're within your line of fire, and a diamond if they aren't."
11049, "(fr)That's enough attacking subsystems for now. Arm your Avenger, and only the Avenger. [Press $.$]"
11050, "(fr)Destroy the transport. No mercy for rectangular boxes!"
11051, "(fr)A wing of Vasudan Isis transports have been added to the simulation. The Isis is the Empire's analog of our Elysium, but sacrifices cargo space for a second turret. Target them with the Target Closest Friendly control. [Press $F$]"
11052, "(fr)Take a look at your target view. Notice that these transports' cargo shows as $quoteunknown$quote. That means you can scan them. Close to within 150 meters and keep your target within your center reticule to scan it."
11053, "(fr)This transport appears legitimate. Now scan the other two. Again, use the Target Closest Friendly control [$F$]."
11054, "(fr)This transport is carrying Hammer of Light terrorists! Switch to Disruptors, target the engines, and disable it before it can escape!"
11055, "(fr)The Hammer of Light transport has been disabled. Normally, we'd deploy a capture team. This time, I'll just delete the transports from the simulation."
11056, "(fr)I'm sure you noticed the Isis's turrets returning fire. The Vasudan Navy's affinity for heavily armed transports was a thorn in our side during the Fourteen Years War. Even after the ceasefire, Hammer of Light terrorists continue to make effective use of these ships."
11057, "(fr)Before we begin the combat section of this simulation, I'd like to review primary linking. Arm both your Avenger and Disruptor. [Press $.$]"
11058, "(fr)Good. Fire a few shots into empty space."
11059, "(fr)Now arm your Avenger only."
11060, "(fr)Fire a few more shots. Observe the effect on your rate of fire."
11061, "(fr)As you can see, linking your primaries causes both banks to fire at roughly three-quarters their usual rate. Linking yields higher damage over time, but can make it harder to hit smaller, more agile targets. Always be mindful of your current weapon configuration."
11062, "(fr)I've created a wing of unarmed drones. They won't attack or try to defend themselves, but will evade when you get too close. Remember to use your hostile targeting control [$H$] or auto-targeting [$Alt-H$] as you attack Poissons wing."
11063, "(fr)Observe the indicators in front of your target. These indicate where you should fire to hit the target based on its current velocity."
11064, "(fr)Well done. You'll now come under attack by multiple waves of armed drones. I've restored your secondary ammunition. Defend yourself!"
