11172, "(fr)Welcome to SCS-1-Delta, Advanced Training. In this simulation, you will learn to transfer power between ship systems and break enemy missile lock."
11209, "(fr)Well done. In battle, linking the Flail with a conventional cannon can be an effective way to prevent an enemy fighter from retaliating. Sustained Flail fire can also strip away a target's shields, making them even easier prey."
11174, "(fr)Consider yourself fortunate that this is a simulation, cadet."
11175, "(fr)Observe how your weapon capacitors recharge from your reactor. This is a passive process that doesn't normally require your attention. However, when using weapons with high power draw, like the Banshee, it can be helpful to divert additional reactor power."
11176, "(fr)Your Energy Transfer System, or ETS, gauge shows the current power distribution between your weapons, shields, and engines. Divert all available energy to weapons. [Press $Insert$ repeatedly]"
11177, "(fr)Good. Observe how your weapon energy recharges more quickly. Diverting energy has no effect on damage, but allows for longer sustained fire."
11178, "(fr)Now route all available energy away from weapons. [Press $Delete$]"
11179, "(fr)Good. Observe that your weapon capacitors no longer regenerate, and the energy has been balanced between your shield and engine systems."
11180, "(fr)Before we go any further, reset your ETS. You can do that manually, but there's a dedicated control for it as well. Try it now. [Press $Alt-D$]"
11181, "(fr)I've placed a waypoint on your escort list. Set your throttle to full, engage your afterburner, and fly towards it. Remember to pulse your afterburner for maximum efficiency."
11182, "(fr)Good. Now, direct all available energy to engines. [Press $Page Up$]"
11183, "(fr)I've moved the waypoint back over here. As you fly back, pay attention to the effect your ETS settings have on your speed and afterburner recharge rate."
11184, "(fr)Now direct all energy away from engines. [Press $Page Down$] Fly around and observe the difference. Reset your ETS when you're ready to move on."
11185, "(fr)For this next part, I'm going to drain your shield energy. Observe how it regenerates over time."
11186, "(fr)The shield setting on your ETS influences how quickly your shields regenerate. At the minimum setting, your shields will not regenerate at all. Try it now. [Press $End$]"
11187, "(fr)Route all energy to shields and observe how quickly they regenerate. [Press $Home$]"
11188, "(fr)There's more to go over with shields, but first, reset your ETS one last time."
11189, "(fr)Fighter shields are derived from captured Shivan technology. This gives them a number of poorly understood quirks. Most notably, you may have noticed that your shield is divided into four quadrants."
11190, "(fr)Each shield quadrant regenerates independently. Observe what happens as I drain your forward shields."
11191, "(fr)You can also redirect energy between shield quadrants. I have drained three of your shield quadrants. Direct all shield energy to the rear. [Press $Down Arrow$]"
11192, "(fr)Lastly, you can equalize all four quadrants. Try it now. [Press $Q$]"
11193, "(fr)Now direct all shield energy to port. [Press $Left Arrow$] Similar shunts are available for forward and starboard."
11194, "(fr)Well done. One last note about shields: they do not function in subspace. This was a key factor in the destruction of the Shivan Lucifer, the only known shielded warship to date."
11195, "(fr)I've added a Canberra-class tactical carrier, the Thug, to the simulation. The Canberra is an open-source design developed to give security contractors leverage against Shivan fighters. Since the end of the Shivan Incursion, they're mostly used by law enforcement and pirates."
11196, "(fr)The Thug's missile launchers will help us practice evasion. A combination of sharp maneuvers and anti-missile countermeasures are the most effective way to break enemy missile lock. Deploy a countermeasure now. [Press $X$]"
11197, "(fr)I'm about to switch the Thug's IFF to hostile. When it fires missiles at you, hit your afterburners and deploy countermeasures until they lose lock. The closer the missile, the more effective your countermeasures."
11198, "(fr)Evade for $ThugTimer seconds"
11199, "(fr)Stay within a kilometer of the Thug."
11200, "(fr)Well done. I've reset your hull and countermeasures to full. You may choose to practice again or move on to the next phase."
11201, "(fr)Press $1$ - Conclude countermeasure training"
11202, "(fr)Press $2$ - Repeat countermeasure training"
11203, "(fr)Note that countermeasures, like missiles, can be resupplied by a support ship. Lastly, we'll go over some advanced weapons. Obtain aspect lock on the Thug."
11204, "(fr)Good. The Hornet swarm missile doesn't track targets quite as well as the Interceptor, but inflicts heavy damage. This makes it a viable choice in a dogfight and in an anti-shipping role. It's often equipped by the Hercules assault fighter and Apollos in an offensive role."
11205, "(fr)Set your Hornets to single-fire mode and fire a volley at the Thug."
11206, "(fr)Switch to double-fire mode and fire another volley. Observe the volume of fire."
11207, "(fr)We have just one more thing to go over. Arm your Flail rifle."
11208, "(fr)The Flail is an unusual weapon. It inflicts moderate shield damage, but is mostly of interest for its kinetic effect. Use your Flail to push me into the Thug's rear hangar. I've moved the waypoint to a good firing spot."
11250, "(fr)One of the convoy ships has been destroyed."
