11262, "(fr)Welcome to SCS-2-Bêta, Combat Gauntlet. In this simulation, you will fight waves of simulated enemy strikecraft. I will act as your wingmate. Begin by ordering me to cover you."
11263, "(fr)Good. Let's get warmed up. A wing of drones is arriving. I recommend enabling auto-targeting. [Press $Alt-H$]"
11264, "(fr)Well done. Next, we'll face some Mustang fighters. These are older fighters, mostly operated by private security groups, but some find their way into pirate hands. Remember to use your afterburner or countermeasures [$X$] to break missile lock."
11265, "(fr)As before, my fighter cannot be destroyed, but I will be removed from combat if I take critical damage."
11266, "(fr)A wing of Pie interceptors is arriving. Like the Mustang, this is an older design mostly fielded by security contractors and pirates. They are highly agile, so consider unlinking your primaries."
11267, "(fr)All targets eliminated. You're doing well. Remember to avail yourself of the support ship, should you need it."
11268, "(fr)So long as the cease-fire remains in effect, ships of the Parliamentary Vasudan Navy are not valid targets. However, the Hammer of Light terrorists, also known as the $quoteHoL$quote or $quoteHolly$quote, operate the same classes. For this next phase, we will practice against HoL ships."
11269, "(fr)A wing of Anubis fighters is arriving. These are roughly comparable to the Terran Mustang. Destroy Bélier wing."
11270, "(fr)Well done. Now, let's up the stakes. The Thot is the Vasudan analogue of the Ulysses. Ever since the Hammer captured the Sahr shipyards in Altair, the Thot has been their fighter of choice. Destroy Verseau wing."
11271, "(fr)For this last phase, we'll be attacked by Seth assault fighters and Horus interceptors. Keep your wits about you and stay agile, and you'll do fine."
11272, "(fr)All Hammer of Light targets eliminated. Well done. Remember, in the field, always check IFF before engaging unknown Vasudan ships. Any action which endangers the cease-fire will spell a quick end for your career."
11273, "(fr)You have successfully completed this training$semicolon however, there is an optional epilogue available, should you wish to further test your skills. If you elect to continue, your hull and ammunition will be restored to full."
11274, "(fr)Press $1$ - Conclude training "
11275, "(fr)Press $2$ - Continue training "
11276, "(fr)You have done well, cadet. Initiate subspace to end this simulation."
11277, "(fr)It is believed that some remnants of the GTI rebellion have joined up with pirate outfits to avoid arrest. We will attack a simulation of one such unit."
11278, "(fr)Our target, the Antagonist, is a Protubérance-class gunship. These are commonly used by both lawful and unlawful paramilitary groups. It's quite far away, so we'll attack it through subspace. Jump when ready."
11279, "(fr)The Antagonist is dead ahead. Two Lokis have arrived to escort it. The attack is yours to command."
11280, "(fr)The escort is down. Target the Antagonist's missile launchers [press $K$] or weapons subsystem [press $S$] with aspect-seeking missiles to disarm it from range."
11281, "(fr)The Antagonist has been destroyed. Clear the blast zone!"
11282, "(fr)That's one less pirate gang for the universe to worry about. Well done."
